## DEVELOPMENT RESULT ARTIFACT — PROOF REQUIREMENTS

You MUST submit a `development_result` artifact before declaring completion. The artifact must include proof for every plan step and every prior analysis how_to_fix item:

**plan_items_proven** (required when the execution plan has steps): One unique entry per step.
- `plan_item`: Canonical step reference — must EXACTLY match "Step N: <title>" where N is the step number and <title> is the step title as written in the plan.
- `proof`: Concrete evidence, e.g. "Modified src/validation.py lines 10-25. All tests pass."

**plan_items_proven** (required when the plan uses work_units): One entry for the work unit you were assigned.
- `plan_item`: Must EXACTLY match the `unit_id` of your assigned work unit from the plan.
- `proof`: Concrete evidence of what you implemented for this work unit.

**analysis_items_addressed** (required when ANALYSIS FEEDBACK exists): One unique entry per `how_to_fix` item.
- `how_to_fix_item`: Must EXACTLY match the how_to_fix text from the prior analysis artifact — copy it verbatim, do not paraphrase.
- `proof`: Concrete evidence of how it was resolved.

Each `plan_item` and each `how_to_fix_item` must be distinct — duplicate entries will fail validation. Unknown references (ones that don't match an actual plan step, work_unit id, or analysis item) will also fail validation and trigger a re-prompt.
